6:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP server GMs and guides</span><hr size=1> I'd call the tech support line, and get in touch with the guy in charge of PvP part of the guide program. I hear that this is often more effective then petitioning, because this way you're starting at the very top and working <i>down</i> the chain of command rather then up, as well as not having to get as hassled about why you are "probing" within the guide progrom plus you won't have a guide dismiss your request for whatever reasons.<br><br>I won't say I've ever done this myself, but I hear it's better then petitioning.<br><br>EDIT: Also, the head GM is very anti-crossteaming. The Order of the Black Rose (rogue only any race guild) attempted to start a chapter on TZ (they are already on RZ and VZ) and the head GM refused to let them create the team simply because he knew they would crossteam.<br><br><br> <p><center><hr width=110 color="red"><hr width=210 color="red"><b>Canbik Virulentus</b><br><font size=-1>36<sup>th</sup> Rogue Warden of Rallos Zek</br>Last Knight and Guild Leader<br>of Silent Decree<br></font><hr width=210 color="red"><hr width=110 color="red"><br><font size="-1"><i>"Its not that I dont think you have the guts to come to rallos, I<br> just want you to come so I can kick yer arse is all."</i>-Diabalein Avidya</font></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.13thshadowcompany.com/svimages/new_post.gif BORDER=0> at: 5/12/01 8:28:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umadelinetz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ma