span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/13/01 7:49:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP server GMs and guides</span><hr size=1> As a guild of rogues was described in the Deathgate Cycle: "We care not for the slant of a man's eyes, but for the glint of his gold."<br><br>Seriously, a rogue doesn't give a flute about someone's race, they're in it for the cash ;p Anyway, true RP would be based on religion, then class, and lastly race. From that standpoint, a crossteaming rogue guild is more roleplaying then virtually every other guild heh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufscsaber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FSC Saber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/13/01 10:23:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP server GMs and guides</span><hr size=1> Madeline from what i've heard your guilds standing with gms is much worse than just receiving harsher treatment. While some members are descent people you guys still let plenty of low lifes in that are ruining things for ya. Best bet is to boot the people prone to xp killing for fun, and ninja looting.  On the whole the I've seen various gms take one side and tend to stick with it through their career on tallon. Most the gms who I thought were fair left or were removed from Tallon.  The biggest prob is it's hard to remain neutral on a teambased server.<br><br>Rainne<br>58th Rogue<br>Tallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umadelinetz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madeline TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/14/01 3:28:31 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/kayden/personalpiccolor.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP server GMs and guides</span><hr size=1> It's actually a misconception about our guild that we are any more &quot;bad&quot; then any other guild.  It's simply the fact that were the center of controversy.  We get petitioned on a daily basis for PKing.  I mean the very basic idea of our server.<br><br>None of us XP kill for fun nor go to ninja loot.  Heck we get better equipment on ddaily runs then most the rest of the server gets on their major runs.  But since were going against the grain we get put under the magnifying glass.  Also remember most of our members are power gamers so their time online is more then most people's so their names hold stronger merit.<br><br>The quality of player and trustworthyness of my guild is much more then any other guilds I have bene in.  I think we've only had internal issues with 2 of our members in our entire career.<br><br>Despite all this though, we shouldn't be unfairly treated just cause he are members of a guild that is against the grain of most the server.  We have just as much right to play as everyone else.  The main GMs on the most part are able to handle themselves perfassionally but it's the guides that are on a power trip.<br><br><br>On a recent raid we had a piece of armor that was fairly nice drop for us in the middle of the battle.  So then this level 2 gnome jumps down and loots it while were fighting.  We petition and the response from the guide was as follows.<br><br>&quot;It was your fault for leaving the loot on the corpse&quot;<br><br>The gnome then trained us twice trying to retrieve his corpse causing near wipeouts of our guild.  The GM then assists him in retrieving his corpse, lets him keep the loot, transport him out of the zone (there was no way out for him other then GM help) and gives him a simple warning.<br><br>Now what is with this particular situation?  Why is some level 2 gnome allowed to ninja loot, train repetedly, and cause almost 2 hours of delay on a raid and allowed to get a slap on the wrist less then if he had used a word that would be filtered on this board?  He also gets a piece of armor that a main tank in our guild would have used at level 55.<br><br>Guides need to be filtered better on Tallon Zek.  I'd rather the guide have stayed out of it cause in 5 minutes, that gnomes efforts would have been for naught.  They also act as if they are enforcing a set of rules oficial by verant yet they aren't suposed to be doing anything of the kind.<br><br>Just pisses me off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarkennvelgarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkenn Velgarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~rosebug67/_uimages/Innoruuk03.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/14/01 11:53:48 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://d.velgarn.tripod.com/brapier.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP server GMs and guides</span><hr size=1> <br>Not on pvp, but damn, that really sucks....  I hope something gets done about this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslinkerdread.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SlinkerDread</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/14/01 12:39:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP server GMs and guides</span><hr size=1> My comment was that on a